# Graphics Rules

## Module Structure

```
libs/graphics/
├── backend/
│   ├── opengl.rs    # ALL raw OpenGL calls live here (gl:: namespace)
│   ├── types.rs     # GPU-side type mappings
│   └── mod.rs
├── sprite_batch.rs  # SpriteBatch — efficient 2D sprite rendering
├── renderer3d.rs    # 3D renderer — primitives, lighting, camera
└── mod.rs
```

## Backend Isolation

- ALL raw `gl::*` calls MUST go through `backend/opengl.rs`
- No other module may call OpenGL functions directly
- Backend exposes safe Rust abstractions over unsafe OpenGL operations
- `types.rs` defines GPU-side type mappings (vertex formats, buffer types)

## Renderer Selection

Runtime renderer selection at `GoudGame` initialization:
- **2D**: `RendererType::Renderer2D` — sprites, 2D camera, Tiled maps
- **3D**: `RendererType::Renderer3D` — primitives, dynamic lighting, 3D camera

## SpriteBatch (2D)

- Batches draw calls to minimize GPU state changes
- Groups sprites by texture for efficient rendering
- Handles sprite transforms, colors, and texture regions
- Camera: orthographic projection via 2D camera system

## Renderer3D

- Renders geometric primitives (cubes, etc.)
- Dynamic lighting system
- 3D camera with perspective projection
- Transform hierarchy applies to 3D objects

## Shader Programs

- Shaders loaded via asset system (GLSL vertex + fragment pairs)
- Compile → link → validate pipeline
- Shader compilation errors must be reported, not silently ignored

## Texture Management

- Textures loaded via image crate (PNG, JPG)
- Texture handles use generational `Handle<T>` pattern
- Texture atlas/region support for sprite sheets

## Testing

- Tests requiring OpenGL context MUST use `test_helpers::init_test_context()`
- Math/logic tests (matrix operations, projections) must NOT require GL
- Texture tests may need valid image files in `assets/`
- Many graphics tests may fail in CI without a display — guard appropriately
